title: King cobra captured after terrorising US town
text:
Miami - A dangerous king cobra that panicked a Florida community has been recaptured, found under a household drying more than a month after escaping, authorities said on Thursday.
The venomous snake, named Elvis, escaped from its owner on September 1 in Ocoee, Florida, prompting a frantic search and calls for people to exercise extreme caution.
Three animal services officers struggled to capture the 3m snake on Wednesday, after a concerned resident reported hissing sounds from beneath a dryer in her garage, Orange County Animal Services said in a statement.
"I attempted to put the snake in my snake box but it was too large to fit," said Billy Ledford, a county animal services officer.
